  "texts": [
    "Then the growth of wages and long-run labor shares are characterized by two thresholds on the rate of automation λg:",
    "If λg > A-ρ-δ η then lim t→∞ w t = A and the labor share converges to zero.",
    "Table 2: Parameter values for the numerical illustration A-ρ-δ η is proportional to the long-run savings rate of the economy.",
    "In the rst case, if the rate of task automation λg is too high compared the savings rate, then the automation index I crosses the threshold Î in nite time and the economy transitions into region 2, where wages collapse to A and remain stagnant.",
    "If the rate of task automation λg is at an intermediate value, then wage growth is constrained by capital accumulation."
